CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, national edition, October 16, 1943, pg. 11, reads: "Nation's Outstanding Women Gather For Elaborate Christening!  Pictured here is a group of the innumerable widely-known women, leaders in civic and social affairs from all sections of the country, who travelled thousands of miles to see Mrs. Robert L. Vann christen the Liberty Ship 'Robert L. Vann' at Portland, Maine. Fashionably attired, they stand in shipyard waiting the thrilling moment when the bottle is broken and the magic words are pronounced. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Toki Schalk (Johnson), two unknown women, Mable Page Johnson, Daisy Lampkin, Jessie Vann, Blanche Morris, and Harriet Lewis turned toward side in center, standing in front of stone building for christening ceremony of the SS Robert L. Vann, Portland, Maine
